verse_content.Word_by_word:
mātrā—sensuous; sparśāḥ—perception; tu—only; kaunteya—O son of Kuntī;
śīta—winter; uṣṇa—summer; sukha—happiness; duḥkha-dāḥ—giving pain;
āgama—appearing; apāyinaḥ—disappearing; anityāḥ—nonpermanent; tān—
all of them; titikṣasva—just try to tolerate; bhārata—O descendant of the
Bhārata dynasty.
